\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"declaration-of-a-function\">&nbsp;Declaration Of A Function<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>int foo(int arg1, int arg2);<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>While a function in many programming languages typically returns a single value, you can use pointers, structures, or arrays to effectively return multiple values or a complex data structure that summing up  multiple pieces of data. This allows you to extend the capabilities of your functions and provide more comprehensive results.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using a pointer to a structure or an array is a powerful technique for returning multiple values of different types or multiple values of the same type. It allows you to bundle related data together, making your code more organized and readable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p> While a function in many programming languages typically returns a single value, you can use pointers, structures, or arrays to effectively return multiple values or a complex data structure that encapsulates multiple pieces of data. This allows you to extend the capabilities of your functions and provide more comprehensive results.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using a pointer to a structure or an array is a powerful technique for returning multiple values of different types or multiple values of the same type. It allows you to bundle related data together, making your code more organized and readable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"faq-how-can-i-return-multiple-values-from-a-function\">FAQ- How Can I Return Multiple Values From A Function?<\/h2>\n\n\n<div id=\"rank-math-faq\" class=\"rank-math-block\">\n<div class=\"rank-math-list \">\n<div id=\"faq-question-1695384251475\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q1. How many values can a function return?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. In many programming languages, only a single value can be returned directly from a function. If you attempt to return more than one value from a function using a <code>return<\/code> statement, typically, only the rightmost value in the return statement will be returned as the function&#8217;s result. However, the behavior may vary depending on the specific programming language you are using.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1695384261790\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q2. Can a function return 3 values?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. In JavaScript, a function can only return a single value directly. However, you can indeed return multiple values by compressing  them within an array or an object and then returning that array or object from the function.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1695384312567\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q3. Can a function return different types?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. in C++, the return type of a function cannot be overloaded. This means that you cannot have multiple functions with the same name in C++ that differ only by their return types. C++ does not support function overloading based solely on the return type.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>How Can I Return Multiple Values From A Function? Returning multiple values from a function is a common programming challenge, often encountered when you need to provide more than one piece of information as the result of a function call. In many programming languages, including C++, Python, and JavaScript, functions are typically designed to return &#8230; <a title=\"How Can I Return Multiple Values From A Function?\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/how-can-i-return-multiple-values-from-a-function\/\" aria-label=\"More on How Can I Return Multiple Values From A Function?\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":2072,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":